        -:   19: they are represented by Cartesian coordinates (intrinsically and possibly extrinsically). The class supports either direct raw fields (just a list of vectors in each
        -:   20: tangent space in order), or power and polyvector fields, representing fields as root of polynomials irrespective of order.
        -:   21: 
        -:   22: This class assumes extrinsic representation in 3D space.
